<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>on the rope • on the ropes</xh5><p> <i>on the rope</i>—(of mountain climbers) roped together: At about 6 we got to where we could unrope—having been 48 hours <u>on the rope</u>.</p><p><i>on the ropes—</i>1. <i>(of a boxer)</i> forced back on to the ropes: Referee Brimmell stepped in to save Scot after the challenger had pinned him <u>on the ropes</u> for fully a minute. 2. on the verge of ruin or collapse: A good section of the industry was <u>on the ropes</u> and there were times when I wondered if it would survive. 3. <i>= on the rope: </i>If they can’t pass some of the slow climbers <u>on the ropes</u> ahead of them, they could run out of time ... and oxygen.</p> </entry>
